org.cloudgraph.state

Class TypeEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cloudgraph.state.TypeEntry

  • public class TypeEntry
extends java.lang.Object
    A key/value map structure mapping type identifiers to integral sequence numbers. If an abstract type is used, then each entry must indicate the derived non-abstract type to use for instantiation of data objects.

    This an other mappings within the state structure are designed and included for the purpose of consolidation of potentially repetitive data which would otherwise be included within cells as column data or as part of composite column qualifiers.

    Since:
    0.5.2
    Author:
    Scott Cinnamond
    See Also:
    URIMap, TypeMapEntry
